SIMPLE: celestial
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Celestial
<hw>Ce*les"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>celestial</ets>, <ets>celestied</ets>, fr. L. <ets>caelestic</ets>,
fr. <ets>caelum</ets> heaved. See <er>Cell</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Belonging to the a⟦eum⟧rial regions, or visible heavens.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The twelve <xex>celestial</xex> signs.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the spiritual heaven; heavenly;
divine.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Celestial</xex> spirits.⟦rdquo⟧
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Celestial</xex> light,⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of, pertaining to, or characteristic of, the
Chinese, or Celestial, Empire, of the Chinese people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Celestial city</b></col>, <cd>heaven; the heavenly
Jerusalem.</cd> <au>Bunyan.</au> -- <col><b>Celestial empire</b></col>,
<cd>China; -- so called from the Chinese words, <xex>tien chan</xex>,
Heavenly Dynasty, as being the kingdom ruled over by the dynasty
appointed by heaven.</cd> <rj><au>S. W. Williams.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Celestial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Celestial
<hw>Ce*les"tial</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An inhabitant of
heaven.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A native of China; a Chinaman; a Chinese.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Celestialize</ent>⟦br⟧
